==English==
===Etymology===
Greek ''[[άνά]]'', "up to", + ''[[λόγος]]'', "ratio".

==== Adjective ====
'''analogue'''
#{{notcomparable}} Of a device, using a continuous spectrum of values as opposed to a set of discrete values; as, an analogue watch.

=====Spelling variants=====
*[[analog]] (''US'')

=====Antonyms=====
*[[digital]]

